news.title: Builders urge Supreme Court for faster environmental clearance evaluations
news.para: A Bench led by Justice JB Paridiwala said that it will hear the real estate body's plea with the main petition on the issue on April 23.

news.title: Three more FIRs against Ansals for property fraud in Lucknow
news.para: The complainants alleged that the realtor neither registered the properties in their names nor handed over possession, despite taking substantial payments years ago.

news.title: SC halts demolition of illegal construction in DLF phases in Gurugram
news.para: The division bench of justices JK Maheshwari and Aravind Kumar ordered a status quo, slamming the brakes on all current and planned enforcement measures until the next hearing, slated four weeks from now.

news.title: After 10 year delay, Unitech set to restart work on six projects in Gurugram
news.para: The six projects — Alder Grove Villas, Espace Premiere Villas, Exquisite Group Housing, Nirvana Country-2 Plots, The Willows Plots and Nirvana Courtyard-2 (commercial) — were launched in 2009 but came to a halt in 2014 due to regulatory hurdles and severe financial distress.

news.title: Adani Group buys land parcel in South Mumbai's Carmichael Road for Rs 170 crore
news.para: The land parcel, which is among the rare large freehold plots available in the highly sought-after neighbourhood, currently houses an old residential cottage spread over 2,760 sq ft. The acquisition has been executed through Adani Group subsidiary, Mah-Hill Properties.

news.title: Lucknow development body opens registration for Anant Nagar scheme
news.para: Interested applicants can register through LDA's official website, registration.ldalucknow.in. The scheme consists of eight khands—Akash, Alekh, Ashish, Abhash, Alok, Adarsh, Aditya, and Amod.

news.title: Residents of AECS Layout in Bengaluru take fight to two illegal constructions
news.para: On Friday, however, when BBMP personnel arrived at the spot to execute the demolition work, the builders produced a high court order staying the notices.

news.title: Illegal construction can’t be tolerated: Bombay HC tells Ulhasnagar civic body, cops
news.para: "We are of the view that the UMC as well as the police authorities are responsible for not taking timely action and thereby promoting and perpetuating the illegal constructions," said Justices Ajay Gadkari and Kamal Khata.

news.title: Karnataka homebuyers alert RBI to irregularities in bank approvals
news.para: KHBF convener Dhananjaya Padmanabhachar compiled observations on banks and submitted them to the RBI, urging it to issue suitable guidelines to safeguard homebuyers’ interests.

news.title: Mumbai: FIR on RA Associates' seven directors for Rs 65 crore investment fraud
news.para: In his complaint, businessman Rajesh Shah of Multiline Corporation alleged that the Kothari brothers of RA Associates in 2015 collected money from him after promising lucrative returns.

news.title: NGT directs Greater Noida authority to act against projects violating norms
news.para: NGT was hearing a plea alleging that in violation of the environmental norms, various illegal constructions of houses, shops and other commercial establishments were in progress in Greater Noida and Noida.

news.title: MMRDA gets Rs 3,840 crore from auction of three plots in Mumbai's BKC
news.para: Japanese firm Sumitomo Corporation's Indian arm, Goisu Realty Pvt Ltd, emerged as the highest bidder for Plots C-13 and C-19, while a consortium led by Schloss Bangalore Ltd bagged Plot C-80, they said.

news.title: UK construction industry faces sharp decline amid weak orders and rising costs
news.para: There was also concern among firms about the impact of the increase in social security contributions paid by employers, the weak outlook for the economy, and geopolitical uncertainty.

news.title: Chennai: GCC to implement new C&D waste management guidelines from April 21
news.para: Residents undertaking minor home repairs or discarding broken ceramic sanitaryware such as tiles, bathtubs, and washbasins can now dispose of their waste free of charge at 15 designated locations across Chennai.

news.title: Average US rate on a 30-year mortgage dips to 6.64% for the second time in two weeks
news.para: The average rate has mostly trended lower since reaching just over 7% in mid-January. When mortgage rates decline, they boost homebuyers' purchasing power.

news.title: India’s office leasing market sees 5% growth in Q1 2025: Report
news.para: Driving this growth was the banking, financial services, and insurance (BFSI) sector, which recorded an over 100% YoY surge in leasing activity, accounting for 26% of total absorption during the quarter.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM inaugurates 800-acre Anant Nagar housing scheme in Lucknow
news.para: The 800-acre Anant Nagar project, developed with an investment of nearly Rs 7,000 crore, is strategically located near the international airport, expressway, and Lucknow Ring Road.

news.title: Bird Group’s Roseate Hotels & Resorts acquires property in UK
news.para: Bird Group executive director Gaurav Bhatia said: “We are beyond delighted to welcome Beechfield House and its exceptionally talented team into the Bird family.

news.title: Subhash Ghai sells two apartments in Mumbai for ₹11.61 crore
news.para: Ghai sold both apartments for ₹5.80 crore each, with each flat having a carpet area of 889 sq ft (82.59 sq meters) and a built-up area of 1,067 sq ft (99.14 sq meters).

news.title: Aastha Group wins The Economic Times Real Estate Award 2025 for Affordable Housing
news.para: Aastha Group received the Economic Times Real Estate Award 2025 for its affordable housing project, Aastha Valley. The project offers homes starting at ₹18 lakh and created many jobs while boosting the local economy. The group is expanding in Jamshedpur with various high-rise and commercial projects, emphasizing premium yet affordable housing.
